  "title": "pypptx thumbnails command",
  "agent_type": "planner",
  "description": "Adds a `thumbnails` command to pypptx that renders each slide of a .pptx file as a JPEG and stitches them into a labeled grid image for visual inspection. The pipeline uses LibreOffice (soffice) for PDF conversion, pdftoppm for per-page JPEG rendering, and Pillow for grid assembly. Hidden slides appear as hatched grey placeholders to keep slide numbering consistent. Pillow is an optional dependency installable via `pip install 'pypptx[thumbnails]'`.",
